Analog/Mixed Signal RF IC Design Engineer - Singapore
Working for a world leading Singapore based R&D; organisation, this is a superb opportunity for a highly qualified (PhD) and experienced RF IC design Engineer.
You will have the opportunity to undertake complex and challenging work in the research and development of integrated circuit designs in advanced Silicon-based technologies.
Experience is required in RF IC Design in CMOS, RF ID tags/readers such as power management, regulators and modulators. A good understanding of RF circuits and Systems is required as well as antenna design, simulation and evaluation.
The successful applicant will be PhD qualified (or equivalent) in a relevant Science/Engineering field. Fresh PhD graduates are welcome to apply.
Remuneration will include a high basic salary and excellent benefits, including relocation and allowances.
Contact Leon at IC Resources today to apply.
Key words: Research focussed position for PhD qualified candidates with RF IC Design Engineering experience. Areas of interest RF IC Design in CMOS, RFID tags/readers such as power management , regulators and modulators. A good understanding of RF circuits and systems is required as well as antenna design, simulation and evaluation, Singapore, Far East.
